headline: Boeing (BA) Valuation In Focus As Recent Share Gains Contrast With Intrinsic Discount Estimate
summary: With no single headline event driving the story today, Boeing (BA) is drawing attention for its recent share performance and financial profile, prompting investors to reassess how its current valuation lines up with ongoing business challenges. See our latest analysis for Boeing. At a share price of $247.68, Boeing has seen a 15.7% 30 day share price return and a 44.77% 1 year total shareholder return. This may indicate building momentum as markets reassess its risks and recovery...

headline: Does Delta Air Lines' Q4 Earnings Beat Justify a Buy Decision Today?
summary: DAL beats Q4 earnings and revenue estimates, driven by international demand and premium sales, but rising labor costs and valuation risks temper buy appeal.

headline: EU Eyes Tariffs on €93 Billion of US Goods Over Threat
summary: The EU is also weighing additional countermeasures beyond the tariffs but will first try to find a diplomatic solution, according to people familiar with the discussions.  Representatives from the EU’s 27 countries met Sunday to begin preparing options.  EU leaders will hold an emergency meeting in Brussels later this week to explore possible retaliatory measures.
